task.summary: I have update Zujian's version which store GWAC data in per line with cache. The cache can cache the inteval data at a later time. The program can send GWAC data using multi-thread and every thread only sends part of cache data at current inteval time. And, in the next inteval time, threads only send the next part of data.
I have update Zujian's version which store GWAC data in four modes. The important mode is perBlockAsaString.

Based on "fourModes" version, I add the random abnormal star generater and interval index (ICDE 2013) which is used for indexing the abnormal stars. At current, I will store the original star data in redis list, and the abnormal star in redis list (one star per list) and the interval index in redis hash.
Question: 1. redis list is not convenience to query by the time range. 2. when generating many abnormal star and their mag, the generater is slow using a single thread.

MESSAGE.value: I use using cmake to manage the project and name it "astroDB_cache" 1.0v. The previous version is managed by xu yang with "make".

I have update Zujian's version which store GWAC data in per line with cache. The cache can cache the inteval data at a later time. The program can send GWAC data using multi-thread and every thread only sends part of cache data at current inteval time. And, in the next inteval time, threads only send the next part of data.
I have update Zujian's version which store GWAC data in four modes. The important mode is perBlockAsaString.

Based on "fourModes" version, I add the random abnormal star generater and interval index (ICDE 2013) which is used for indexing the abnormal stars. At current, I will store the original star data in redis list, and the abnormal star in redis list (one star per list) and the interval index in redis hash.
Question: 1. redis list is not convenience to query by the time range. 2. when generating many abnormal star and their mag, the generater is slow using a single thread.

Based on "fourModesAndGenAbnormalStarAndIntervalIndexV1.2" version, I do not store original star table into Redis and only store the star_id and mag to save memory. Second, I store template table into Redis with the block id and partition it into many blocks as the space index.Third, I store original star into local disk tentatively. I do this according to the speedup layer of Lambda architecture.

Based on "fourModesAndGenAbnormalStarAndIntervalIndexV1.3.1" version, I add the lower left and top right coordinates for each block to ascertain their locations. At location query, their locations can help us to filter some unnecessary blocks.
